9 (b) "Primary substance misuse prevention" means preventing the initiation of substance abuse or
10 delaying the age of initiation to prevent health problems before they occur by:
11 (i) addressing risk factors;
12 (ii) enhancing resistance to those risks; and
13 (iii) shifting the focus to help people avoid, reduce, or modify drug use.
