15 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Marijuana impact report. The marijuana tax revenue accountability
16 council DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES shall provide a written marijuana impact report in
17 accordance with 5-11-210 to the children, families, health, and human services interim committee, the
18 economic affairs interim committee, and the law and justice interim committee, no later than September 1 of
19 each year. The report must include:
20 (1) public health and safety objectives that may be impacted by marijuana policy changes,
21 including prevalence and patterns of use; and
22 (2) information on harms, including but not limited to cannabis use disorder, marijuana
23 hospitalizations, environmental impacts of marijuana production, licenses, marijuana business density,
24 marijuana law enforcement actions, criminal and administrative violations, youth access, and cases of driving
25 under the influence of marijuana.
