12 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Marijuana law enforcement office. (1) There is a marijuana law
13 enforcement office in the department of justice under the supervision and control of the attorney general
14 division of criminal investigation.
15 (2) The office shall conduct law enforcement operations related to marijuana, including but not
16 limited to combatting black market activities and investigating and prosecuting criminal violations of marijuana
17 regulations related to illicit manufacture, distribution, diversion, and trafficking of marijuana and other related
18 criminal violations.
19 (3) The office must include:
20 (a) two marijuana enforcement teams, one based in western Montana and one based in eastern
21 Montana; and
22 (b) a district attorney; and
23 (c) a canine unit
24 (b) one deputy attorney general prosecutor assigned to support the office as needed.
25 (4) The office is funded with revenue from the marijuana law enforcement operations account
26 provided for in [section 4 2].
